12:20.211 --> 12:21.377
Now he's just a bummer.

12:21.379 --> 12:23.579
It's not like I want
to be a bummer.

12:23.581 --> 12:26.099
I just... I have to be.

12:26.101 --> 12:27.583
I'm gonna be a dad.

12:27.585 --> 12:28.851
You'll have kids someday.

12:28.853 --> 12:29.969
You'll understand.

12:29.971 --> 12:32.588
Dude, I have four kids.

12:32.590 --> 12:35.758
Pete, please take
the video down.

12:36.777 --> 12:38.778
All right, Beercules,
I'll take the video down.

12:38.780 --> 12:40.229
If...

12:40.231 --> 12:43.316
you can best me in
a game of my own choosing.

12:43.318 --> 12:44.567
Oh, no...

12:44.569 --> 12:47.036
And I select the beautiful game,

12:47.038 --> 12:48.270
the sweet science...

12:48.272 --> 12:50.072
Pete, please,
I'm so hungover...

12:50.074 --> 12:51.157
...the sport of kings...

12:51.159 --> 12:53.126
I don't want to play
"Edward Forty Hands."

12:53.128 --> 12:54.276
I was gonna say darts--

12:54.278 --> 12:57.079
but "Edward Forty
Hands" it is!

12:57.081 --> 12:59.882
And that concludes all
the space-related lies.

12:59.884 --> 13:02.585
Let's move on to
the world of sports.

13:02.587 --> 13:05.555
Oh, wait, sorry-- I just thought
of another space one.

13:05.557 --> 13:07.890
"I've been bitten
by a moon snake.

13:07.892 --> 13:10.459
You need to suck all the
space poison out of my--"

13:10.461 --> 13:12.145
Okay, Barney, uh,

13:12.147 --> 13:13.679
I have to be at work
tomorrow at 8:00,

13:13.681 --> 13:15.348
which means I have
just about enough time

13:15.350 --> 13:17.750
to sit in a shower for 11 hours,
hugging myself.

13:20.087 --> 13:21.237
So this was fun.

13:21.239 --> 13:22.455
Can I call you, or...?

13:22.457 --> 13:25.608
Barney, you're funny, handsome

13:25.610 --> 13:27.276
and really quite clever.

13:27.278 --> 13:29.445
But you're also a sociopath.

13:29.447 --> 13:31.347
Well, I count three pros
and one con, so...

13:31.349 --> 13:33.833
How do you still think
you have a chance with me?

13:33.835 --> 13:36.169
Because you sat
here all night.

13:36.171 --> 13:38.321
You could've left right
away, but you didn't.

13:39.289 --> 13:43.759
Look, Nora, all those lies--
that's the old me.

13:43.761 --> 13:46.562
But I swear to you,
I am trying to change.

13:46.564 --> 13:50.466
You... make me want to change.

13:50.468 --> 13:53.352
How do I know that's not a lie?

13:53.354 --> 13:55.071
I'll prove it.

13:55.073 --> 13:56.939
I will prove how serious I am.

13:56.941 --> 13:59.675
I will not leave this diner

13:59.677 --> 14:02.879
until I get
a second date with you.

14:03.981 --> 14:05.198
Good-bye, Barney.

14:05.649 --> 14:07.033
I'm not kidding.

14:07.035 --> 14:08.484
This is a 24-hour diner.

14:08.486 --> 14:12.121
I'll stay here forever,
if I have to-- and I will!

14:13.991 --> 14:15.691
Just water for me. Thanks.

14:18.194 --> 14:20.997
Okay, so red indicates
level of attractiveness,

14:20.999 --> 14:23.466
blue--
intellectual stimulation,

14:23.468 --> 14:25.051
green-- emotional connection,

14:25.053 --> 14:27.703
yellow-- compatibility
of life goals,

14:27.705 --> 14:31.206
and purple-- whether or not
she reached for the check.

14:32.042 --> 14:33.643
Well, it looks like
Jessica's ahead

14:33.645 --> 14:35.711
in the first
four categories.

14:36.881 --> 14:40.416
Did not reach for the check...

14:42.853 --> 14:44.053
Oh, this?

14:45.222 --> 14:46.722
No big deal. This...

14:46.724 --> 14:48.357
This cost three
months rent,

14:48.359 --> 14:50.026
and, uh, I've never
gotten to wear it,

14:50.028 --> 14:52.862
because I bought it for that big
event that you invited me to,

14:52.864 --> 14:54.396
which then fell through.

14:54.398 --> 14:55.831
But, you know what?

14:55.833 --> 14:57.450
Don't feel guilty about that.

14:57.452 --> 14:58.417
What big event?

14:58.419 --> 14:59.568
That thing with your uncle.

14:59.570 --> 15:01.354
His funeral?

15:02.089 --> 15:03.205
It didn't fall through,

15:03.207 --> 15:04.707
he miraculously
came out of a coma.

15:04.709 --> 15:06.509
And I forgive you.

15:06.511 --> 15:09.095
Now, can I please
meet Lenny Kravitz?

15:12.415 --> 15:13.883
I did it again!

15:13.885 --> 15:15.801
Aw, honey.

15:15.803 --> 15:17.086
You got drunk again.

15:17.088 --> 15:19.722
I can't believe
I took the over.

15:19.724 --> 15:24.193
Just to be clear, "I did it
again" is not a reference...

15:24.195 --> 15:26.762
to my current state of
inebriation.

15:26.764 --> 15:28.931
What's it a reference to?

15:28.933 --> 15:30.900
My name is Marshall Eriksen.

15:30.902 --> 15:32.885
I'm 33 years old.

15:32.887 --> 15:37.957
And if my potential future
employer, Garrison Cootes,

15:37.959 --> 15:40.442
is watching this...

15:40.444 --> 15:43.129
bow down to Beercules!

15:50.087 --> 15:51.921
Well, that could
be anybody.

15:57.363 --> 15:58.695
Oh, goodness.

16:06.077 --> 16:07.986
Pete, this is Lily Aldrin.

16:07.987 --> 16:09.720
I'm gonna make this real simple:

16:09.722 --> 16:11.572
You're gonna take down
that video of Marshall.

16:11.574 --> 16:12.973
You know why?

16:12.975 --> 16:16.026
Because I'm friends with three
girls who dated you in college,

16:16.028 --> 16:18.528
and girls
tell each other everything.

16:18.530 --> 16:21.215
Every <i>tiny</i> detail.

16:21.217 --> 16:22.533
Huh. So...

16:22.535 --> 16:27.888
tick-tock, Pete-- tick-tock goes
the little wee-wee clock.

16:28.757 --> 16:29.873
Pete's got a little wee-wee?

16:29.875 --> 16:31.592
No idea.
What's everyone getting?

16:31.594 --> 16:34.762
This was bound to
happen eventually.

16:34.764 --> 16:37.731
I've been trying so hard
to suppress, like,

16:37.733 --> 16:39.383
my carefree idiot side,

16:39.385 --> 16:43.220
that it just rebelled
and came out swingin'!

16:43.222 --> 16:44.388
It sure did.

16:44.390 --> 16:46.774
Look at me! I'm a windmill!

16:46.776 --> 16:49.944
Who am I kidding?
I'm not ready to be a dad.

16:49.946 --> 16:52.780
I thought that I was,
but it's, like...

16:52.782 --> 16:55.916
my dad never did stuff
like that, you know?

16:55.918 --> 16:57.401
So what if he did?

16:57.403 --> 16:59.286
You'd still love him.

16:59.288 --> 17:02.923
And be honest-- wouldn't you
love to stumble onto a video

17:02.925 --> 17:05.442
of him running down
the street naked, yelling,

17:05.444 --> 17:07.176
"Hey, Marshall, look at me!

17:07.179 --> 17:09.696
I got an icicle on my deal!"

17:13.935 --> 17:15.219
Oh! Hey, guys!

17:15.221 --> 17:16.920
Ow! My neck!

17:16.922 --> 17:19.390
Uh... oh! Hey!

17:19.392 --> 17:20.808
Look at that.

17:20.810 --> 17:23.426
Barney, what are
you doing here?

17:23.429 --> 17:26.530
Oh, I told Nora I wouldn't leave
until she gave me a second date,

17:26.531 --> 17:27.815
and I mean it.

17:27.817 --> 17:29.266
I've already been here
nine hours.

17:29.268 --> 17:32.036
I still need
another minute.

17:32.038 --> 17:35.289
I mean... call me crazy, but

17:35.291 --> 17:37.891
I'm gonna stay here until
I get that girl back.

17:40.611 --> 17:43.797
That-- that's
what I want.

17:44.716 --> 17:46.300
The way Barney
feels about Nora--

17:46.302 --> 17:47.951
I want that feeling again.

17:48.953 --> 17:50.838
I don't want to be choosing
between two girls,

17:50.840 --> 17:55.642
I want to be... a complete
head-over-heels idiot for one.

17:55.644 --> 17:57.728
Yeah, the complete
head-over-heels idiot thing's

17:57.730 --> 17:59.897
pretty nice.

18:00.982 --> 18:02.316
It's not bad.

18:02.318 --> 18:05.102
Although, for the record--

18:05.104 --> 18:08.572
sweeping declaration!--

18:08.574 --> 18:13.494
I am never getting
drunk again.

18:14.413 --> 18:16.430
<i>And sure enough...</i>

18:16.432 --> 18:18.332
All hail Beercules!

18:19.719 --> 18:21.018
Yeah!

18:21.020 --> 18:23.704
